    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-16T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-16T07:00:00-05:00" n="379"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/1106: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-16T21:00:00+09:00"
                            >October 16, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 16—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1643. It was officially announced at 8:15 this evening that the resignation of
                    the entire Cabinet had been submitted to the Emperor at 5 o’clock this
                    afternoon. The Emperor has requested the Cabinet to remain in office for the
                    time being.<note n="18" xml:id="d379fn18">In his telegram No. 1650, October 17,
                        5 p.m. (894.00/1107), the Ambassador in Japan informed the Department that
                        General Hideki Tojo, Minister of War in the fallen Konoye Cabinet, had been
                        commissioned to form a new government.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
